<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Jimette on 01-22-2002 10:02 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">One finger salute to Verant

We tried to tell you a year ago, but you wouldn't listen. Me, my guild leader and a friend spent a total of 124 hours camping that son of a bitch for my epic.

How much you want to bet the number of people coming back after the SOL lucin is way under their hoped for rate, and it's time to start offering more bribes.

Just goes to show that you can be nice to Verant, and they ignore you until the $ starts to stop going in

Ex-Jimette 60th Cleric
EQ-Free for 4 months and counting

BTW, after we got our epic, and after watching around 30 spawns, our guildleader pointed out that after the death of Naggy, there was 3 different spawn patterns with fixed spawn possibilities at a certain pattern of hours that lead to between 2 and 3 Ragefires per week. 

I think the numbers were (and this is digging in to long term memory so the numbers could be wrong):

For one spawn pattern, there was around a 25% chance that Ragefire would spawn at (for example) 8 hours, 24 hours, 48 hours, 72 hours, 80 hours, 104 hours, 148 hours, 172 hours after a Naggy death.

There was three different spawn patterns, with a minimum spawn of 2 hours from Naggy death and we never saw a spawn of more then 148 hours. The trick was finding out the first spawn or two, figuring out the spawn timer, then assembling a raid force on each time he had a chance of popped, rather then keeping them there the whole time.

We used this successfully to get around 20 cleric epics.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
